<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Tatarstan Pleased With Power-Sharing Treaty </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Tatarstan Pleased With Power-Sharing Treaty </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2006091694 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0903 GMT 20 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2006091694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Nikolay Sorokin] </F>
  [Text] Kazan June 20 TASS -- Vice-President of Tatarstan 
Vasiliy Likhachev characterised the Russian-Tatarstan 
power-sharing treaty as a "most functional document". He 
praised Russian President Boris Yeltsin's decree ordering the 
foundation of a committee to regulate the implementation of the 
treaty. An analogous committee has already been formed in 
Tatarstan. 
  The vice-president said his republic's treaty with the 
Russian Federation was the first document in Russia's history 
which established constructive cooperation between a region and 
the centre. He noted that the Tatarstan commission already has 
a specific programme for the agreement's realisation. For 
example, Tatarstan plans to play a role in federal-level 
economic programmes, such as the ones for the production of 
Tu-204-200 aircraft, cars, and oil-tankers. 
  Yeltsin's decree is a significant step forward in the 
implementation of radical reforms aimed at turning Russia into a 
truly democratic federation, Likhachev commented. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

