<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   FCIS To Ensure Security in Nakhodza Free Economic Zone </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    FCIS To Ensure Security in Nakhodza Free Economic Zone </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1806165494 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1523 GMT 18 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1806165494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Federal Counterintelligence Service (FCIS) 
intends to take an active part in ensuring security in the free 
economic zone Nakhodka situated in Russia's Far East. 
  Chief of the FCIS Public Relations Center Aleksandr 
Mikhailov 
reported to Interfax Saturday that Director of the service 
Sergey Stepashin who was on an inspection trip throughout this 
region this week commissioned local counterintelligence officers 
to fulfil this task. 
  In Mikhailov's words, separate criminal clans use the 
opportunities of the free economic zone to inflict damage to the 
economy of the country as a whole and to the economy of the Far 
East in particular. 
  Stepashin called counterintelligence officers to adopt all 
necessary measures to ensure normal functioning of Nakhodka free 
economic zone. 

</TEXT>

