<H3> <TI>   Roundup on Provincial Affairs </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Roundup on Provincial Affairs </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MK1706121094 Moscow SEGODNYA in Russian 17 Jun 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> MK1706121094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow SEGODNYA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Untitled, unattributed reports under the "Provincial </F>
Chronicle" rubric] 
  [Text] Kazan -- A plenipotentiary mission of Tataria 
[Tatarstan] in Russia has been instituted by an edict of the 
republic's president. Nail Aminov, deputy chairman of the 
Russian Federation State Committee on Federation and 
Nationalities Affairs, has been appointed envoy plenipotentiary. 
  Cheboksary -- Chuvashia President Nikolay Fedorov has 
suspended by edict some of the articles in the republic's law on 
the dismantling of state ownership and privatization of 
republican and municipal property. At the same time he has 
pointed out that there will be no major changes in the 
privatization policy. 
  Khabarovsk -- The local kray committee of the Communist 
Party 
of the Russian Federation has circulated a statement on 
Russo-Chinese relations which says in part that the expansion of 
bilateral relations should take account of the Far Eastern 
territories' interests and the inviolability of the existing 
borders. The Communists demand that the Russian Federation 
Government denounce the 1991 border treaty and hold talks with 
the Chinese side with the participation of representatives of 
the kray. 

</TEXT>

