<H3> <TI>   KGB Official Says Attempt `Staged' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    KGB Official Says Attempt `Staged' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1806170094 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1555 
GMT 18 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1806170094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by BELINFORM correspondent for TASS] </F>
  [Text] Minsk, 18 Jun -- There was no attempt made on the 
life of People's Deputy Aleksandr Lukashenko, a candidate in the 
Belarus presidential elections, Petr Snopok, the press secretary 
of the Belarus KGB, said today speaking on behalf of the 
Committee for State Security at a news conference. 
  It was announced at the news conference, in which Deputy 
Interior Minister Lyutsian Sobolenskiy and Vasiliy Targonskiy, 
KGB senior investigator for special cases, participated, that 
the shooting at the car in which Aleksandr Lukashenko was 
travelling was staged. The information gathered from an 
investigative experiment and the contradictory stories given by 
those who were with Lukashenko bear witness to this, it was said 
at the news conference. 

</TEXT>

