<H3> <TI>   Refugees Settle in Gomel Oblast Radioactive Villages </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Refugees Settle in Gomel Oblast Radioactive Villages </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM2006130794 Moscow IZVESTIYA in Russian 18 Jun 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> PM2006130794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow IZVESTIYA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [ITAR-TASS report: "Refugees Occupy `Radioactive' Villages"] </F>
  [Text] Under the onslaught of refugees from Central Asia 
the Gomel Oblast authorities have been obliged to "open up" 
villages clogged with radioactive weeds. 
  Having learned of the opportunity for acquiring housing, 
refugees are rushing here from the CIS trouble spots. They come 
knowing that the local inhabitants are subject to enforced or 
voluntary removal. They are fleeing poverty and dobule-dyed 
nationalism and, they say, are choosing the lesser of two evils. 
In all of last year alone, about 2,300 people including over 700 
children arrived in radioactive Gomel Oblast. This year the 
oblast took in a further 300 refugees. 

</TEXT>

