<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-SOV-94-118 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  17 Jun 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> WESTERN REGION </F>
<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   Outbreak of Disease Afflicted Swine Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Outbreak of Disease Afflicted Swine Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS1706134994 Minsk Radio Minsk Network in Belarusian 1200 
GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS1706134994 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk Radio Minsk Network </F>
<F P=105>  Belarusian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Epidemiologists in Brest are alarmed. In some 
villages near the center of the oblast, outbreaks of an 
especially dangerous and infectious disease -- swine plague 
[chuma sviney] -- have been recorded. This is an unusual 
incident, because the disease wipes out pigs of any breed and 
any age. The (?greatest) danger is posed by the meat of the 
infected pigs, which are being slaughtered. Their meat may only 
be safely used after thermal processing and even then, only for 
preparing stewed sausages and canned meat. 
  The Brest Rayon Executive Committee has imposed a quarantine 
in all infected regions. During this quarantine, all exports 
and imports of pigs, as well as the grazing of cattle at 
collective farms, are forbidden; transportation movement is also 
limited. Other regions of the oblast are also alarmed; free, 
large-scale swine vaccination campaigns are already being 
implement in those areas. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

