<F P=100> CENTRAL ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Kazakhstan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Nazarbayev Chairs Session of Security Council </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Nazarbayev Chairs Session of Security Council </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1706170994 Almaty Kazakh Radio Network in Kazakh 1400 GMT 
17 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1706170994 </F>
<F P=104>  Almaty Kazakh Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Kazakh </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A regular Security Council session, chaired by 
President Nazarbayev, was held yesterday. At issue were 
questions related to the state of equipment of the Armed Forces 
of the Republic of Kazakhstan with technology, armaments, 
material, and technical resources. The concept of formation and 
implementation of long-term defense programs and development of 
the defense complex of the Republic of Kazakhstan were also 
examined. General Sagadat Nurmagambetov, the defense minister, 
and Economy Minister Mars Urkumbayev presented reports. An 
exchange of opinions was held, summed up by Nursultan 
Nazarbayev: We must precisely decide what an army needs -- how 
many men we need -- he said. We should urgently tackle all 
questions connected with equipping the Armed Forces, we should, 
to a maximum degree, reduce import of military products from 
outside, and to the best of our possibilities manufacture such 
products in Kazakhstan. The head of state set an objective--in 
one week's time--to set up a commission on the military 
industry. Its chairman will be directly responsible for the 
situation in this important sphere, which should provide 
reliable defense capability for our sovereign state. 
  By their decision, the Security Council approved of the 
concept of formation and implementation of long-term defense 
programs and development of the defense complex. The council 
also endorsed several changes in its membership. In particular, 
Bulat Baekenov was appointed secretary of the council. 
  Speaker Abish Kekilbayev, Akizhan Kazhegeldin, first deputy 
prime minister, Deputy Prime ministers Galym Abilsiitov and 
Asygat Zhabagin, and heads of a number of ministries and 
departments, as well as responsible officials from the 
presidential administration and that of the Cabinet of Ministers 
participated in the session. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

