<F P=101> Kazakhstan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Nazarbayev Sends Message to Cooperatives Union </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Nazarbayev Sends Message to Cooperatives Union </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1806130094 Almaty Kazakh Radio Network in Russian 0100 GMT 
18 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1806130094 </F>
<F P=104>  Almaty Kazakh Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] A meeting of the union of Kazakh consumer 
cooperative societies was held in Almaty on 17 June. [passage 
omitted] The union is the largest in the Central Asian system, 
which ensures reliable provision to the rural population of 
food, industrial goods, and various services. It is a powerful 
organization that purchases agricultural raw materials and 
provides quality prosessing of it in a most beneficial way. It 
is a full-fledged member of the International Cooperative 
Alliance. Its Kazkoopvneshtorg branch maintains direct trade 
contacts with companies of 35 foreign countries. 
  Deputy Prime Minister Sergey Kulagin read out a greeting 
from 
President Nazarbayev. The union of consumer societies, it says, 
have come a long way; its history has been inseparable from that 
of our state. At each stage of the country's development, 
cooperatives made a significant contribution in the improvement 
of the rural population's living standard and strengthening of 
ties between the city and the village. 
  The president suggested that the members of the Republic's 
cooperatives, using their long experience of organization of 
market relations, should quickly restructure their work in 
conformity with the demands of the times. 

</TEXT>

