<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A massive meeting organized by the Attan public 
movement was held yesterday in Almaty in front of the Chinese 
Embassy to Kazakhstan. The participants of the meeting were 
protesting against nuclear tests held at the Lop Nur testing 
site, which is located only 300 km away from the Kazakh border. 
Multiethnic participants of the meeting expressed support for a 
statement released by the Kazakh Foreign Ministry in connection 
with the explosion at Lop Nur. 
  Kazakhstanis are especially concerned about these tests 
because they have suffered for over 40 years from the tests at 
the Semipalatinsk site and are worried about the fate of their 
future generations. The Kazakh people, who have contributed so 
much to the closure of the Semipalatinsk site, are protesting 
together with the peoples of Kyrgyzstan and Uzbekistan, who also 
border on China. There are no borders to protect us against 
nuclear radiation and its consequences. The meeting and rally, 
which began yesterday in front of the Chinese Embassy, will 
finish on 29 August in New York in front of the UN headquarters. 

</TEXT>

