<F P=100> Tajikistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ready for Cease-Fire </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ready for Cease-Fire </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1806210794 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 2000 GMT 
18 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1806210794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Tajik opposition is ready to sign an agreement 
on a cease-fire along the Tajik-Afghan border for the period of 
the inter-Tajik talks, Otakhon Latifi, the head of the Tajik 
opposition delegation at the inter-Tajik talks in Tehran, told 
INTERFAX on Saturday [18 June]. The opposition intends to 
present a draft of such an agreement to the delegation 
representing official Dushanbe at the second round of 
inter-Tajik talks that have opened in Tehran. It plans to look 
for ways of settling the political situation in Tajikistan 
peacefully, to examine the problem of the return home of all 
Tajik refugees, and the issue of the future constitutional 
system. The talks are being held under UN auspices. 

</TEXT>

