<F P=100> Tajikistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Three Militiamen Killed, 12 Wounded in Ambush </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Three Militiamen Killed, 12 Wounded in Ambush </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2006061694 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0530 
GMT 20 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2006061694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondent Galina Gridneva] </F>
  [Text] Dushanbe, 20 June -- Three members of the militia 
staff were killed and 12 wounded during the day on Sunday [19 
June] as a result of a clash that occurred in the mountainous 
Fayzabad rayon of Tajikistan. Besides this, the fate is still 
not known of two militia men whose bodies were not discovered at 
the scene of the exchange of fire. 
  The staff of the internal affairs directorate of the 
neighboring (Kofarnihan) rayon were the victims of an attack by 
one of the bandit formations. According to information from 
Tajikistan's Ministry of Internal Affairs the group of militia 
staff were ambushed while on an official assignment. A criminal 
case has been instituted with regard to the crime. 

</TEXT>

