<F P=100> CAUCASUS </F>
<F P=101> Armenia </F>
<H3> <TI>   CSCE's Eliasson Arrives in Yerevan </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    CSCE's Eliasson Arrives in Yerevan </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1706203794 Yerevan Armenia's Radio First Program Network 
in Armenian 1900 GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1706203794 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan Armenia's Radio First Program Network 
in Armenian 1900 GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=105> Armenian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] As already reported, the CSCE Minsk Group delegation 
dealing with the Nagorno-Karabakh problem arrived in Stepanakert 
on 16 June headed by Jan Eliasson. 
  The Nagorno-Karabakh Republic [NKR] Press and Information 
Department reported that the CSCE delegation held a meeting on 
the same day with Karen Baburyan, acting chairman of the NKR 
Supreme Council; Robert Kocharyan, chairman of the State Defense 
Committee; and Foreign Minister Arkadiy Gukasyan. 
  Jan Eliasson told reporters that regrettably the conflicting 
sides have different views regarding the future steps aimed at 
resolving the conflict. He said that the CSCE Minsk Group is 
thinking of continuing its efforts in cooperation with the 
Russian Federation to bring the positions of the conflicting 
sides nearer. 
  The CSCE delegation visited the front lines and the 
prisoners 
of war held in Stepanakert this morning. The talks continued 
between the Minsk Group delegation and NKR leadership in the 
first part of the day. 
  After the conclusion of the talks, Jan Eliasson and members 
of the delegation left Stepanakert for Yerevan in the afternoon. 
  Jan Eliasson and his delegation were received by President 
Levon Ter-Petrosyan late tonight. Details of the meeting will 
be aired during our newscasts tomorrow. 

</TEXT>

