<F P=100> CAUCASUS </F>
<F P=101> Armenia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Parliament Passes State Enterprise Privatization Order </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Parliament Passes State Enterprise Privatization Order </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1806201194 Yerevan SNARK in English 1646 GMT 18 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1806201194 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan SNARK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Business SNARK" file] </F>
  [Text] Yerevan [dateline as received] -- The Presidium of 
Armenian Supreme Council has determined by its resolution "the 
order of partial unpaid privatization of the state enterprise 
property, and their transformation into joint-stock companies". 
According to this document, the property ownership certificate 
shall be granted to the personnel who served for more than one 
year at a particular enterprise. The share of each stock-holder 
is determined in the certificate and depends on the average 
salary, total length of service, and some other factors. 
  Privatization order has been developed by the Armenian 
Government under the law "On Privatization of State Enterprises 
and Unfinished Buildings", according to which 20 percent of 
fixed assets of privatized enterprise may be freely passed to 
its staff. 
  At the same time, a long list of more than 300 enterprises 
was approved by the Presidium, that are not subject to unpaid 
privatization. The list includes, in particular, those Armenian 
state enterprises which function on the territory of other CIS 
countries. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

