<H3> <TI>   `Zone of Trust' Proposed for Border Area </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Zone of Trust' Proposed for Border Area </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   944K1493A Yerevan RESPUBLIKA ARMENIYA in Russian 16 Jun 
94 p 1 </F>

<F P=103> 944K1493A </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan RESPUBLIKA ARMENIYA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
CSO 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Instead of Zone of Conflict--Zone of </F>
Trust"] 
  [Text] In keeping with a prior agreement, a meeting of 
Armenian and Nakhichevan delegations, headed by David 
Shakhnazaryan, the Republic of Armenia president's special envoy 
and chief of the Republic of Armenia state directorate for 
national security, and the chairman of the Nakhichevan Council, 
Namik Gasanov, met on 14 June in the border area of Eraskhevan. 
  Participating in the meeting were the Republic of Armenia 
chief border commissioner Gegam Arutyunyan and representatives 
of military units and executive authority of Ararat and Sadarak 
Rayons. 
  As we were told at the press center of the Republic of 
Armenia Ministry of Defense, the Nakhichevan side once again 
admitted that its military units were at fault in the incident 
that took place on 27 May on the border of Ereskh. 
  With the purpose of averting such border incidents, the 
Armenian delegation proposed to turn the border zone between 
Armenia and Nakhichevan into a zone of trust, and as the first 
practical step in this direction to set up border trade points 
here. 
  The Nakhichevan side promised to present this proposal to 
the 
Azerbaijani leadership for consideration. 

</TEXT>

