<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Baku, June 17 (SNARK)--The Azerbaijani Defence 
Minister Mamadrafi Mamedov denied the mass media reports on the 
fact that there, in Moscow, are going on the negotiations 
between the Russian, Armenian and Azerbaijani military experts. 
  In the interview to "Radio Svoboda" he reported, that these 
days the representatives of these countries' foreign policy 
departments meet in Moscow. Touching upon the Russian plan of 
the Karabakh conflict settlement the minister mentioned that 
Moscow wants to be useful as a mediator but there are certain 
points Azerbaijan can't accept. Mamedov again confirmed the 
traditional demands of the official Baku - to set the occupied 
territories free. Answering the question about the situation at 
the front, Mamedov was more than brief: "At the front everything 
is all right". 

