<H3> <TI>   U.S. Secretary of State's Letter to Gasanov Cited </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    U.S. Secretary of State's Letter to Gasanov Cited </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1806184594 Baku TURAN in English 1710 GMT 18 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1806184594 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku TURAN </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Baku, June 18 (TURAN)--A letter of U.S. State 
Secretary Warren Christopher sent to Gasan Gasanov, Azerbaijan 
Foreign Minister reads that Christopher appreciates adoption by 
Azeri Government the last proposal of CSCE Minsk group, which 
provides ceasefire and location of observers in the region. 
Christopher notes in the letter that the Azerbaijan agreement 
with CSCE proposal witnesses Azerbaijan's intention to peaceful 
settlement of Karabakh conflict. "We demanded from Armenia and 
Karabakh Armenians to accept this proposal as well", notes 
Christopher. 
  The letter reads that representatives of U.S. Government, 
addressing at the Congress expressed their unsatisfaction by 
Article 907 of the Act support of freedom. According to 
Christopher "despite that, it would be very difficult to take 
away limitations imposed by Congress on the providing assistance 
to Azerbaijan". Christopher also supported U.S. readiness to 
help the CSCE Minsk group. 

</TEXT>

