<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Head of CSCE Minsk Group on Karabakh Peace Process </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Head of CSCE Minsk Group on Karabakh Peace Process </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1806183694 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1738 GMT 18 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1806183694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondents Sevindzh Abdullayeva, Viktor </F>
Shulman] 
  [Text] Baku June 18 TASS -- It is necessary to fully 
coordinate negotiations on Armenian-Azeri settlement, head of 
the CSCE Minsk group on Nagorno-Karabakh Jan Eliasson said here 
today. 
  Eliasson has returned from Baku upon the completion of 
consultations in Yerevan and Stepanakert and met Azeri President 
Geydar Aliyev tonight. 
  In his opinion, pulled efforts of the sides, the mediating 
missions of CSCE and Russia will help to elaborate a common 
concept of the problem solution. He said that cease-fire in the 
conflict zone has begun an important settlement stage and the 
settlement process should have the right direction. 
  It is also important to prevent a new escalation of combat 
operations. That is why, the persons who are responsible for 
further developments should estimate their chance correctly and 
reach certain compromises in order to settle the conflict 
peacefully and through political negotiations, said Eliasson. 
  The most correct way towards peace is gradual solution of 
problems that have piled up over the conflict years. Each stage 
should be connected with another in a single link, he noted. 
Such a constructive approach will ensure the withdrawal of 
Armenian troops from Azeri lands, return of refugees to places 
of their permanent residence and security guarantees for 
Karabakh Armenians, which is considered the most important in 
the settlement by each side, said Eliasson. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

