<H3> <TI>   Parliamentary Delegation Leaves for Bucharest </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Parliamentary Delegation Leaves for Bucharest </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1706211494 Baku TURAN in English 1741 GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1706211494 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku TURAN </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Baku, June 17 (TURAN)--Today Azerbaijan's 
Parliamentary delegation headed by Vice-Speaker, Afiaddin 
Dzhalilov, left for Romania. The delegation will take part in 
the session of Interparliamentary Assembly of the countries 
belonging to the Black Sea basin. 
  The session is due to take place on June 21 in Bucharest. 
During the session the issues concerning customs, import and 
export operations and economic integration are to be discussed. 
  Dzhalilov also said that the Azeri delegation intends to 
discuss the issues concerning Armenia's aggression against 
Azerbaijan, the blockade imposed by Armenia against Nakhichevan 
and the damage caused to Azerbaijan during Armenia-Azerbaijani 
war. 
  The delegations from Romania, Turkey, Russia, Ukraine, 
Albania, Armenia, Georgia and other countries are expected to 
take part at the session as well. 
  The organization of countries belonging to the Black Sea 
basin was founded in 1992 at the initiative of Turkey. The 
purpose of this organization is establishment of economic and 
mutual advantageous cooperation among the countries belonging to 
the Black Sea basin. 

</TEXT>

