<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kondratyev Explains Requirements for Peacekeeping </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kondratyev Explains Requirements for Peacekeeping </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM1706193594 Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA in Russian 18 Jun 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> PM1706193594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Major Sergey Prokopenko and Colonel Aleksandr </F>
Luchaninov of the Russian Federation Ministry of Defense Press 
Center, from the "KRASNAYA ZVEZDA Correspondents and News 
Agencies Report" roundup: "Commander's Reconnaissance Under 
Way"] 
  [Text] Abkhazia -- Deputy Defense Minister Colonel General 
Georgiy Kondratyev has issued a statement for the press. 
  The arrival at Gudauta Airfield of military-transport 
aviation aircraft does not signify the beginning of a 
peacekeeping operation by the Russian Armed Forces in the zone 
of the Georgian-Abkhaz conflict. This operation can only begin 
after ratification by the Federation Council of the edict by the 
Russian president. The arrival in Gudauta of a signal center 
and combat-engineer battalion was proposed as a preparatory 
stage for the introduction of peacekeeping forces. Their main 
task is to clear the area of mines and to establish 
communications with the command posts. As Colonel General G. 
Kondratyev stated at the meeting with journalists, the 
introduction of Russian peacekeeping forces into the zone 
separating the warring sides may only be effected after the 
adoption by parliament's upper house of the relevant decision. 
  Subunits from the 345th Airborne Regiment stationed in 
Gudauta will not take part in peacekeeping operations. Russia's 
deputy defense minister expressed the hope that a political 
decision by the supreme legislative bodies will facilitate the 
establishment of peace on this land. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-40685 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drsov118_s_94003" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-SOV-94-118 </AU>
Daily Report 
