<H3> <TI>   Right-Wing Forces Meet, Unite in Alliance </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Right-Wing Forces Meet, Unite in Alliance </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS2006101194 Tallinn BNS in English 1539 GMT 18 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS2006101194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tallinn, June 18, BNS -- A meeting of Estonia's 
rightist forces yesterday in the south Estonian town of Voru 
adopted the statutes of the Parem-Eesti (Rightist Estonia or 
Better Estonia) national alliance. Juri Estam, head of the 
Estonian Association of Owners by Law and a well-known 
television personality, was unanimously elected chairman of the 
organization. 
  Parem-Eesti unites right-of-center parties and organizations 
that intend to go to the next parliamentary election on a 
coalition platform. Under the statutes, former members of the 
Communist Party and employees of repressive organs like the KGB 
cannot belong to the leading bodies of the alliance or run in 
election on its ticket. 
  The eight-member board of Parem-Eesti includes, besides 
Estam, representatives from the Estonian National Progress 
Party, the Estonian National Party, and four other rightist 
groups and associations. 

</TEXT>

