  [Text] The Broadcasting Council met today for the first 
time. Rein Veidemann, deputy chairman of parliament's cultural 
commission, was elected its chairman, and Toivo Tasa, 
editor-in-chief of the VIKERKAAR magazine, was elected his 
deputy. One of the council's primary tasks is to appoint 
