<F P=100> UKRAINE </F>
<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Moroz Against Dividing Black Sea Fleet </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Moroz Against Dividing Black Sea Fleet </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1906214994 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 2100 GMT 
19 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1906214994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Oleksandr Moroz, chairman of the Ukrainian Supreme 
Council, has spoken out against the division of the Black Sea 
Fleet. At a meeting with the Crimean Supreme Council deputies he 
proposed that the Black Sea Fleet should not be regarded as an 
object to be divided. 
  According to Moroz, the Black Sea Fleet should be used 
jointly by Ukraine and Russia with the fleet remaining under a 
unified joint command, and with Russia giving orders to one part 
of the fleet and Ukraine to the other. There must be separate 
commands for parts the parts, but a joint command as well, so 
that the fleet should not be demolished as a fighting unit. The 
Black Sea is a special interest zone for Ukraine and Russia. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

