<H3> <TI>   Defense Minister Views Destruction of Missile in U.S. </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Defense Minister Views Destruction of Missile in U.S. </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1806013994 Kiev UNIAN in Ukrainian 2000 GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1806013994 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAN </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kiev -- The press service of Ukraine's Ministry of 
Defense has reported that on 16 June, Army General Vitaliy 
Radetskyy, Ukraine's minister of defense, visited Elsworth 
Airbase (in South Dakota) during his official visit to the 
United States. He viewed the missile launch silo of a strategic 
ballistic missile, which had been prepared for elimination and 
destruction in the presence of the head of the Ukrainian 
military department. Vitaliy Radetskyy evaluated this step as a 
manifestation of confidence in and respect for Ukraine, and also 
as a continuation of mutually beneficial relations between the 
military departments of both countries. 
  On 17 June, Vitaliy Radetskyy met employees of the RAND 
Corporation in Los Angeles. During the conversation he stressed 
that as a guarantee of its national security Ukraine has its own 
armed forces and also its defense industry, which should provide 
the military with armaments and fighting equipment. 

</TEXT>

