<H3> <TI>   Crimean Interior Ministry Refutes Need for Ukrainian Troops </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Crimean Interior Ministry Refutes Need for Ukrainian Troops </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1806162794 Moscow Radiostantsiya Ekho Moskvy in Russian 
1500 GMT 18 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1806162794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radiostantsiya Ekho Moskvy </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] [Announcer Marchenko] Elements of the Ukrainian 
Interior Ministry's special forces arrived in Simferopol last 
night. Aleksey Tkach, deputy head of the Republic's Interior 
Ministry explained the aim of the deployment for our radio 
station. 
  [Begin Tkach recording] Yes, it is true that such an outfit 
was deployed. They are special forces from the 21st special 
detachment. The aim of their transfer is, generally speaking, 
the situation that has emerged in connection with the fact that 
the Crimean golden eagles [berkuty] are not carrying out their 
duties. Around a third of the Crimean golden eagles are busy 
guarding [Crimean President] Meshkov and [Crimean Interior 
Minister] Kuznetsov himself. They are not looking after public 
order. [end recording] 
  [Marchenko] We asked the Crimean interior minister, Valeriy 
Kuznetsov, to comment on this statement by the Ukrainian 
Interior Ministry. 
  [Begin Kuznetsov recording] There is no slacking. The 
Interior Ministry of the Crimean Republic is fulfilling its 
obligations. I will tell you one thing: They [Ukraine] are 
doing everything in their power now to dissolve the Interior 
Ministry of the Crimean Republic, which is against the 
Constitution of the Crimean Republic and even Ukraine's law on 
delegating powers. They are breaking a lot of the laws of both 
Ukraine and Crimea. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

