<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Attempt Made on Life of People's Deputy Candidate </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Attempt Made on Life of People's Deputy Candidate </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1806142894 Kiev UNIAN in Ukrainian 2000 GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1806142894 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAN </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kharkov, [no date as received] -- As a UNIAN 
correspondent learned, on 16 June an attempt was made on the 
life of Oleksiy Stelmakh, age 28, a people's deputy candidate of 
the city council, Constituency No. 70, and editor of the 
independent city newspaper V KAZHDYY DOM [TO EVERY HOUSE] with 
the largest circulation in the city. A stranger accosted him at 
the entrance to the editorial office and hit him several times 
on the head with a heavy metal object, thus inflicting grave 
bodily injuries. The stranger disappeared. 
  In an interview with a UNIAN correspondent Oleksiy Stelmakh 
said he believed this was a political attempt, because his 
chances of winning in the constituency were extremely high. 
  Criminal proceedings have been instituted in connection with 
this attack. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-40709 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drsov118_f_94006" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-SOV-94-118 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  17 Jun 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kuchma Focusing on Taxation, Currency Issues for Elections </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kuchma Focusing on Taxation, Currency Issues for Elections </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1706195694 Kiev UNIAN in Ukrainian 1630 GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1706195694 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAN </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kharkov -- At a news conference for local 
journalists on 16 June, Leonid Kuchma, a candidate for president 
of Ukraine, expressed the opinion that Ukrainian society is 
continuing to live under socialism, that the state is to be 
found on the brink of a national catastrophe, 
deindustrialization of the country is occurring, it is being 
turned into a raw materials appendage, and it is sliding toward 
an African path of development. 
  In the event of his election as president, Leonid Kuchma 
considers his most important steps to be resolving issues of 
taxation policy, the revocation of a fixed currency exchange 
rate, getting banking, credit, and financial activity going, and 
resolving the non-payments problem. In Kuchma's opinion, one 
should conduct forced small privatization and return currency 
from abroad. The candidate for the post of president believes 
that land and all means of production should become goods in 
future, but if one were to declare land to be goods now, one 
could end up with nothing. 
  Once again Leonid Kuchma expressed himself against the 
election of a prime minister before the presidential election, 
and noted that although he considers Vitaliy Masol to be an 
experienced individual, Masol's present views are not known, and 
on the whole he considers "all of this" to be "a dangerous game." 
  At the news conference, Leonid Kuchma renounced some of the 
assertions he made during his previous meeting with 
representatives of the nonstate sector of the economy. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-40710 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drsov118_f_94007" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-SOV-94-118 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  18 Jun 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Criticizes Masol Appointment </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Criticizes Masol Appointment </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1806190994 Kiev UNIAN in Ukrainian 1530 GMT 18 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1806190994 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAN </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kharkov [no dateline as received] -- While in the 
oblast on 17 June, Leonid Kuchma, president of the Ukrainian 
Union of Industrialists and Entrepreneurs and a candidate for 
president of Ukraine, expressed himself critically regarding the 
Supreme Council having elected Vitaliy Masol as the new prime 
minister. He is convinced that this does not demonstrate the 
recognition of this person's authority, but is a manifestation 
of ordinary political games on the eve of the presidential 
election. "If Ukraine's voters elect someone other than Leonid 
Kravchuk or Oleksandr Moroz as president on 26 June, Leonid 
Kuchma stressed, then cooperation between the prime minister and 
the president will be fairly problematical." 
  Leonid Kuchma did not rule out that the last week in the 
presidential marathon will bring much that is unexpected. In 
particular, in his opinion, contenders for the presidential seat 
will withdraw their candidacies. If Oleksandr Moroz does this, 
Leonid Kuchma expressed the hope that his [Moroz's] electorate 
will vote for Leonid Kuchma. In the opinion of Leonid 
Danylovych Kuchma, the forces supporting him in Ukraine's east 
and south should influence changes to the existing state of 
affairs more actively, when in fact western Ukraine is dictating 
its conditions to the whole of the 50 million-strong country. 
  Leonid Kuchma maintained: "If I am not elected, this will 
not 
be a great tragedy for me. On the whole, I am returning to 
politics only in order to save Ukraine. Otherwise, I would not 
risk going into the corridors of power." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

