<H3> <TI>   OTV Cancels Program on Election Candidate Kuchma </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    OTV Cancels Program on Election Candidate Kuchma </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1706162694 Moscow Radiostantsiya Ekho Moskvy in Russian 
1500 GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1706162694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radiostantsiya Ekho Moskvy </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ten days before the presidential election in 
Ukraine, the former Prime Minister Leonid Kuchma is heading the 
list of candidates. According to opinion polls, 31 percent of 
respondents support him. Some 20 percent of Ukrainian citizens 
are ready to support the current president, Leonid Kravchuk. 
  Here is another report indirectly connected with the 
Ukrainian election. The "Person of the Week" program from the 
Vid company under Ostankino TV, which was scheduled for tonight, 
has been taken off the air. It was to have profiled Leonid 
Kuchma. Our radio station has found out that the broadcast was 
cancelled by Gennadiy Shipitko, deputy chairman of the Ostankino 
company responsible for political and information matters. 

</TEXT>

