<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kravchuk in Odessa Views CIS Integration, Economy </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kravchuk in Odessa Views CIS Integration, Economy </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1706180394 Moscow NTV in Russian 1500 GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1706180394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow NTV </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Today, Leonid Kravchuk was on the election trail in 
Odessa. 
  [Correspondent Sergey Barabanov] Ten days are left before 
the 
Ukrainian presidential elections. Observers note a significant 
growth in the popularity of the current President Leonid 
Kravchuk. During his one-day visit to Odessa today, he paid most 
attention to the economy problem, but also dwelt in some detail 
on the prospects for the political integration of CIS countries. 
  [Begin Kravchuk recording] Yes, the time will come, yes, 
there will be integration, yes, there may be political elements 
in the integration. But if this is begun today, then it would 
strain the situation to the limit -- both in Russia and outside 
Russia. I think that certain gentlemen are making haste in 
putting forward new formulas today. We have to use the 
potential of the CIS. [end recording] 
  [Barabanov] As is well-known, Kravchuk's main opponent, 
Leonid Kuchma, holds a different opinion on that point. What 
the people of Ukraine think we will find out on 26 June. 

</TEXT>

