<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Meets German Parliamentarians </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Meets German Parliamentarians </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1906142894 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1343 GMT 19 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1906142894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS] </F>
  [Text] Berlin June 19 TASS -- "Russia and Germany are 
currently going through the process of renewal, which, despite 
many differences, have much in common. In particular, this 
concerns Eastern Germany, which offers broad opportunities for 
cooperation and interaction," said visiting Chairman of the 
Russian State Duma, Ivan Rybkin, addressing representatives of 
the Berlin parliamentary assembly in the "Charlottenburg" Castle 
in Berlin on Sunday. 
  Rybkin expressed his gratitude for the warm and friendly 
welcome given to the Russian delegation, saying that "during the 
period of uneasy economic transformations in Russia cooperation 
with Germany is of great importance." 
  Deputy chairman of the Berlin assembly of lawmakers, 
Reinhard 
Fuerer, said that Germany regards the visit by the Russian 
delegation as a contribution to the development of existing 
contacts and the beginning of new contacts between the two 
countries at a parliamentary level. "Tremendous changes are 
taking place both in Russia and in Germany. The Russian 
Federation has achieved considerable progress on the way to 
democracy. This is worthy of praise even more, taking into 
account a complex process of reforms in the country's economy 
which, at times, poses serious problems to the population. 
However, these problems and additional hardships should not be 
used as a pretext for going back on the process of 
democratisation," the deputy chairman of the Berlin assembly 
said. 
  He pointed out that Russia should take a firm place in free 
europe. "Russia is doing so by taking an active part in U.N. 
peace- keeping actions. Such efforts arouse respect all over 
the world, the German lawmaker said. 
  The chairman of the Russia State Duma made an entry in 
Berlin's "gold book". 

</TEXT>

