<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russian Procurator Ilyushenko Visiting N. Caucasus </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russian Procurator Ilyushenko Visiting N. Caucasus </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Announces Special Procuracy </H4>

<F P=102> LD1706125994 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0646 
GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1706125994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Valeriy Shanayev] </F>
  [Text] Vladikavkaz, 17 June -- A procuracy with special 
powers is to be set up in the state of emergency zone in North 
Caucasus. This was announced on 16 June by Aleksey Ilyushenko, 
acting Russian Federation procurator general, who is visiting 
Vladikavkaz. He said that this decision was made in order to 
ensure that laws are complied with and to coordinate the work of 
investigative bodies. 
  Aleksey Ilyushenko is touring the North Caucasus in order to 
familiarize himself with the situation in the region and to 
prepare proposals for a meeting of the Russian Government which 
will examine progress in implementing Russian presidential 
edicts and cabinet decisions on the return of refugees to their 
former homes. 

</TEXT>

