<F P=100> WESTERN REGION </F>
<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   Assasination Attempt Against Presidential Candidate </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Assasination Attempt Against Presidential Candidate </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1706111294 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1025 
GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1706111294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by BELINFORM correspondent Svetlana Kalinina-TASS] </F>
  [Text] Minsk, 17 June -- On 16 June the car in which 
Aleksandr Lukashenko, presidential candidate and well-known 
campaigner for anticorruption, was shot at after leaving a 
meeting with the electorate. As a BELINFORM correspondent was 
told by Likashenko's spokesman, this happened at midnight near 
the regional center of Liozno in Vitebsk Oblast. Fortunately, 
the bullet from a passing car of foreign make did not hit 
Lukashenko. It just went through the car seat. 
  The shooting was confirmed by the Liozno internal affairs 
directorate. However, no details of the incident have been 
given. 
  Boris Aldanov, Belarusian deputy minister of internal 
affairs, reported that an investigation has begun and said he 
was puzzled why the indicent was reported to the region's 
militia department eight hours after it happened. 

</TEXT>

