<F P=100> Tajikistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Opposition Groups Reportedly Assembling on Afghan Border </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Opposition Groups Reportedly Assembling on Afghan Border </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1706175194 Dushanbe Radio Tajikistan Network in Tajik 1200 
GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1706175194 </F>
<F P=104>  Dushanbe Radio Tajikistan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Tajik </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The information department of the Ministry of 
Foreign Affairs of the Republic told a KHOVAR correspondent that 
armed groups of the Islamic Rebirth Party of Tajikistan have 
assembled in the Badakhshan Province of Afghanistan close to the 
residential areas of Darvoz and Shugnan rayons and the Khorog 
city of the Gorno-Badakhshan Autonomous Oblast of Tajikistan. 
  Their aim is to cross over to the territory of Tajikistan 
and 
wage armed struggles in the future against the government forces 
and to reach the Khoburabot Pass. Mercenaries from other 
countries are also included in the armed groups. 
  Leadership of the Afghan province of Badakhshan, including 
its military commander Abdol Khalid (Basir), are not doing 
anything to stop the movement and operation of the armed groups 
on the Tajikistan-Afghanistan border. 
  Explaining the situation, the headquarters of the group of 
Russian border guards in Tajikistan said that decisive measures 
will be taken against the armed groups attempting to violate and 
cross the border. 

</TEXT>

