<H3> <TI>   Russian Peacekeeping Forces Prepare To Deploy </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russian Peacekeeping Forces Prepare To Deploy </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1706212394 Baku TURAN in English 1741 GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1706212394 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku TURAN </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tbilisi, June 17 (TURAN)--Introduction of the 
Russian peacemaking forces to the Georgian-Abkhazian conflict 
zone has been preparing. 
  Georgian source report that the transportation of the 
Russian 
field-engineering battalion to Georgia began yesterday. 
Beginning in June 19 the battalion will be engaged in mine 
clearing and placing of peacemaking forces in the conflict zone. 
  Two motor-infantry battalions from the Group of Russian 
troops for Transcaucasia have already been transported to 
Georgia. When the Council of Russian Federation passes the 
final resolution concerning this issue, these battalions will be 
introduced into the frontline, along the river of Inguri. 
  Military source also report that Russia and Georgia adopted 
a 
joint resolution concerning restoration of the bridge through 
Inguri river, which has been blown up in 1993 during actions. 

</TEXT>

