BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by UKRINFORM correspondent Aleksey Trotsenko for </F>
TASS] 
  [Text] Kiev 16 June TASS -- Ukrainian Foreign Minister 
Anatoliy Zlenko and his Israeli counterpart Shim'on Peres have 
praised results of the latter's two days' official visit to 
Ukraine. 
  "Successful development of friendship and cooperation 
between 
our countries" was once again reaffirmed during the visit, 
Zlenko told a press conference on Thursday [16 Jun]. 
  According to him, Ukraine became native land for many Jews. 
They made a contribution to Ukrainian culture. 
  In this connection, he mentioned large-scale festivities 
held 
in Ukraine to mark the 135th anniversary of Sholom Aleykhem, a 
classic of Jewish literature. 
  According to Peres, his stay in Ukraine has made a very good 
impression. I am sure we will be able to open a new chapter in 
the development of friendship and cooperation between Israel and 
Ukraine, Peres said. 

