Daily Report 
<DATE1>  18 Jun 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Latest on Implementation of Social Accord Agreement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Latest on Implementation of Social Accord Agreement </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Filatov Addresses Implementation Forum </H4>

<F P=102> LD1806114194 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1036 GMT 18 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1806114194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Tamara Zamyatina] </F>
  [Text] Moscow June 18 (TASS) -- There is a positive thing 
about the public accord treaty: "The political struggle in 
Russia ceases to be a political squabble and becomes a political 
competition," Sergey Filatov, chief of staff of the president's 
administration, said today. He spoke at a meeting of the public 
chamber under the Russian president. The public chamber 
discussed the implementation of the treaty, signed by 863 
representatives of power structures, regions, parties and public 
organisations. 
  Filatov believes at the same time that it is too early for 
democratically-minded reformers to relax in conditions of 
relative political stability. In his opinion, "a period of an 
easy-term credit of confidence for the reformers is over." 
  He urged the like-minded people to combine two principles in 
their ideology -- patriotism and democracy, and on their basis 
to work for accord in society. In order to work out a strategy 
of joint actions, the reformers will hold a forum of democratic 
forces next autumn in Moscow. 
  The purpose of today's meeting of the public chamber was to 
set up five commissions included in it -- on political 
stability, on socio-economic problems, on the federal setup and 
inter-ethnic relations, on the safety of individuals and the 
security of society and on problems of science, education and 
culture. Those commissions were assigned the task of organising 
control over the implementation of the public accord treaty and 
drawing up recommendations to be approved at meetings of the 
public chamber. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

