<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Latest on Implementation of Social Accord Agreement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Latest on Implementation of Social Accord Agreement </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Public Chamber To Have 5 Commissions </H4>

<F P=102> LD1806165394 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1523 GMT 18 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1806165394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Public Chamber under President Yeltsin upheld 
Sergey Filatov's proposal for focusing on the realization of the 
civic accord agreement on June 23. Filatov is the chief of 
staff under Boris Yeltsin. 
  The Public Chamber is to have commissions on political 
stability, social and economic problems, administrative makeup 
and interethnic relations, security, and science research, 
education and culture. 
  The five commissions will be expected to supervise the 
realization of the civic accord agreement and offer advice to 
the conciliatory commission. 
  In Filatov's view, they must have a membership of twenty 
nine 
and bring together representatives of political movements and 
parties, parliamentary factions, public organizations, labor 
unions, religious communities, etc. 
  Arkadiy Volskiy, Mark Masarskiy, Anatoliy Dolganov, Viktor 
Andreyev and Vladimir Kudriavtsev were presented as choices for 
the commission's chairmen. According to Filatov, they represent 
"a wide spectrum of the Russian public" because their political 
affiliations as well as jobs they hold are very different. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

