<F P=102>   LD1906144194 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0943 
GMT 19 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1906144194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 19 June -- By a decision of Russian 
President Boris Yeltsin a commission has been set up on a parity 
basis from representatives of the executive bodies of the 
Russian Federation and the Republic of Tatarstan for the purpose 
of implementing government agreements and the treaty between the 
Russian Federation and Tatarstan on dividing areas of 
responsibility and mutually delegating powers by state bodies of 
the federation and the republic, and supervising their 
fulfilment. 
  By the same presidential decision, which was signed on 
Saturday [18 June], Oleg Soskovets, first vice prime minister of 
the Government of the Russian Federation, was appointed chairman 
of the commission. 

