<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Media Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kozyrev Demands More Responsibility From Media </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kozyrev Demands More Responsibility From Media </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2006103594 Moscow INTERFAX in English 0918 GMT 20 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2006103594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The media can play a negative role in Russia's 
political life, said Russia's Foreign Minister Andrey Kozyrev, 
addressing on Monday the International Conference on the Role 
and Responsibility of the Media in the Development of Democracy 
and Tolerance. 
  "The recent parliamentary elections showed that a pathetic 
political dwarf and scandalous figure can turn into a leader of 
a parliamentary party due to a few snappy appearances on TV," he 
said without disclosing the name of the politician he meant. 
  He believes that the danger of nationalism is still 
threatening the country and that chauvinism and nationalism are 
evident in many democratic publications. 
  He urged reporters to quote official statements more 
exactly, 
providing critical comments on them. "This will help highlight 
the authors' idiocy," he said. 

</TEXT>

