<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Military &amp; Nuclear Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin To Cut State Order to Defense Industry </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin To Cut State Order to Defense Industry </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1806091094 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0907 GMT 18 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1806091094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By itar-tass correspondent tamara zamyatina] </F>
  [Text] Moscow June 18 TASS -- The next package of the 
president's economic decrees will contain a decree on the 
dramatic reduction of mobilisation plans and reserve capacities 
at enterprises of the defence complex. Deputy Prime Minister 
and Minister of Economy Aleksandr Shokhin announced today at a 
meeting of the public chamber under the president of the Russian 
Federation. 
  According to Shokin, the purpose of the decree is to promote 
the working out of a new military doctrine and to reduce the 
state order to the defence industry. 
  It is worth recalling that during his recent tour of the 
country Yeltsin mentioned the forthcoming reduction of the army 
from three million to 1.5 million and urged enterprises of the 
defence complex to take up conversion. "The Russian Army does 
not need a large amount of armaments. It needs mobile military 
hardware, which can stand competition at the domestic and 
foreign markets," the president said. His stand has been 
reflected in the forthcoming decree. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

