<H3> <TI>   Interior Ministry Troops To Be Increased </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Interior Ministry Troops To Be Increased </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1806145894 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1310 GMT 18 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1806145894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The operative units of Russia's Interior Ministry 
troops will be increased by 52,000 men, said President Boris 
Yeltsin, addressing the personnel of the operative division of 
Russia's Interior Ministry troops (the former Dzerzhinskiy 
Division). He took part in celebrating the 70th anniversary of 
the division. 
  Those who attended the festivities also included the 
Federation Council Speaker, Vladimir Shumeyko; the Interior 
Minister, Viktor Yerin; the Foreign Minister, Andrey Kozyrev; 
and the Director of the Federal Counter-Intelligence Service, 
Sergey Stepashin. 
  Boris Yeltsin drew attention to the rampage of crime in the 
country, which, according to him, began to threaten the state 
and individual citizens. He pointed to the need to strengthen 
law and order. 

</TEXT>

