<H3> <TI>   Joint Projects Offered to Malaysia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Joint Projects Offered to Malaysia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0706102094 Moscow RIA in English 0845 GMT 7 Jun 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD0706102094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow RIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kuala Lumpur, June 7, RIA -- Russia regards Malaysia 
as its prime partner helpful in establishing broader relations 
with the entire ASEAN, First Vice-Premier Oleg Soskovets 
announced at the talks with his Malaysian opposite number Anwar 
Ibragim today. 
  Oleg Soskovets also said that Russia has already produced 75 
business offers for Malaysia. The two countries may, in 
particular, conclude an agreement on industrial, scientific and 
technological cooperation. Russia may help Malaysia with power 
production and shipbuilding and jointly manufacture satellites 
with a Malaysian private firm. 
  The chairman of the Defence Industry Committee, Viktor 
Glukhikh, said the two countries may cooperate in environmental 
protection, use of natural resources, medicine, aerospace 
industry, machine- building, shipbuilding, radioelectronics, 
computer industry, communications and dual application 
technologies. 

</TEXT>

