  The resolution ignores the new Russian constitution and 
brings back the atrocities of the 1930s. Mr. Yeltsin's other 
latest decisions are meant to leave the national economy in 
ruins and run counter to his own message on strengthening 
Russian statehood. 
  The communist group also demands the suspension of 
SOVETSKAYA 
ROSSIYA daily revoked by an ad hoc commission to be set up for 
the purpose. 
  The group called former mps from all ex-Soviet republics to 
a 
congress of June 25 to demand the USSR re-established. 

