<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Varennikov Demands Court Examination of August Coup Events </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Varennikov Demands Court Examination of August Coup Events </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0706133694 Moscow RIA in English 1148 GMT 7 Jun 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD0706133694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow RIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, June 7, RIA -- "I want to see the 
examination of the so-called case of the SCSE [State Committee 
for the State of Emergency] through. The people must know the 
truth about the August 1991 events," General of the Army 
Valentin Varennikov, former commander-in-chief of the land 
forces of the USSR, told a RIA correspondent. He is the only 
member of the SCSE to have rejected the amnesty announced by the 
State Duma. He demanded that the trial of his case should be 
continued, and its examination is to be resumed on June 21. 
  Varennikov thinks he is perfectly guiltless. "I shall be 
able 
to do my duty in court, to defend my honour and to give the 
names of those who are actually guilty of disintegrating the 
Soviet Union, an epochal event in the eyes of world history," 
the former commander of the land forces pointed out. He said 
that the court will have to summon as witnesses Mikhail 
Gorbachev, Dmitriy Yazov, Oleg Shenin and a number of other 
persons. "In my turn, I intend to invite to the court some 
politicians involved in the August events, particularly the 
president of Russia, and to testify as witnesses," Varennikov 
added. The general also said that lawyer Dmitriy Shteinberg 
will be his defence attorney, as before. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

