<DOCNO> FBIS4-40772 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drsov119__a94021" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-SOV-94-119-A </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  21 June 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Economic Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chubays Attitude to Moscow-Style Privatization Unchanged </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chubays Attitude to Moscow-Style Privatization Unchanged </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1206164394 Moscow RIA in English 1512 GMT 12 Jun 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD1206164394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow RIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, June 12, RIA -- "I will continue to fight 
for the observance of laws in Russia and I do not want this to 
be called a struggle against Yuriy Luzhkov," Anatoliy Chubays, 
vice-premier of the Russian Government and chairman of the State 
Property Management Committee, told a RIA correspondent during 
an intermission in the founding congress of Russia's Democratic 
Choice Party today. 
  It is to be remembered that President Yeltsin asked First 
Vice- Premier Oleg Soskovets to tell Chubays that he "should not 
have anything to do with Moscow." 
  Chubays promised to do all within "authority to punish those 
who violate laws regardless of their position. Time will show 
who wins. however, my attitude to privatisation Moscow style did 
not change after President Yeltsin's famous order," he said. 

</TEXT>

