<H3> <TI>   Crimean Official Claims National Guard Units Deployed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Crimean Official Claims National Guard Units Deployed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1406111794 Moscow RIA in English 0950 GMT 14 Jun 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD1406111794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow RIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, June 14, RIA -- Ukraine is increasing the 
number of the units of its national guards in the Crimea. Petr 
Chernyatevich, the Crimean president's adviser for military 
affairs, said this in his telephone conversation with a RIA 
correspondent. As has become known just now, he said, the units 
of the Ukrainian national guards have been deployed in 
Yevpatoria and Kerch though this act contradicts the decrees by 
Leonid Kravchuk of April 14 and 26, this year. According to 
these decrees, the Ukrainian national guards should be deployed 
only in Simferopol and Sevastopol. 
  According to the recent data, said the Crimean president's 
adviser, the national guards regiment is being transformed into 
a brigade. 
  Petr Chernyatevich asserts that the Ukrainian authorities 
have not given up their attempts to split the Crimean interior 
forces. They are conducting psychological pressure on them with 
the aim of winning over at least part of the militia personnel 
to their side. 
  The Crimean president's adviser said that this work is 
headed 
by Ukrainian Deputy Interior Minister Nedrigailo. However, the 
local militia are still devoted to the legally elected Crimean 
government. 

</TEXT>

