<F P=103> LD0306165194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow RIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Simferopol, June 3, RIA -- Another round of 
negotiations conducted by the joint working group including 
representatives of the Ukrainian and Crimean Parliaments ended 
in Simferopol today. The group discussed the entire range of 
legal problems arising from relations between the two 
parliaments. The chief negotiators, Aleksey Melnikov, deputy 
chairman of the Crimean Parliament, and Vladimir Butkevich, head 
of the Ukrainian Parliament's Human Rights Commission, told RIA 
that the negotiations had been conducted in a friendly and 
constructive atmosphere. 
  It has been decided to resume the activities of the working 
group shortly and invite experts on legal and economic issues to 
take part in the discussion of specific problems. The deadline 
for the next meeting will be fixed out of session. 

