<F P=102>   LD1006112894 Moscow RIA in English 0826 GMT 10 Jun 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD1006112894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow RIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bishkek, June 10, RIA -- A representative NATO 
delegation, headed by General P. Karstens, supreme allied 
commander Europe, intends to visit the air force base in the 
Kirghiz [Kyrgyz] capital and aviation units in the suburbs of 
Bishkek. The delegation arrived in the republic yesterday 
evening. 
  According to the official version of the Kirghiz Defence 
Ministry's press centre, during its meetings with the republican 
leadership and with the heads of the Defence Ministry, the sides 
will discuss the prospects of the development of equitable and 
mutually advantageous relations and business contacts. 
  However, some local observers assert that one of the 
subjects 
of the discussions will be the deployment of an air force base 
of the Atlantic bloc in Kirghizia [Kyrgyzstan]. This explains 
the delegation's interest in aviation installations. 

</TEXT>

