<H3> <TI>   Visa Requirement Introduced for Czech, Other Citizens </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Visa Requirement Introduced for Czech, Other Citizens </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0806143794 Prague CTK in English 1157 GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0806143794 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow June 8 (CTK) -- The Tajik Government has 
decided to request visas from citizens of Lithuania, Latvia, 
Estonia and the Czech Republic as of June 15, the news agency 
ITAR-TASS announced today from Dushanbe. 
  The Czech Embassy in Moscow told CTK today that the Tajik 
measure had not been officially announced to it. 
  Since the split of Czechoslovakia on December 31, 1992, the 
visa for Czechs have been introduced only by Uzbekistan, to 
which Prague reacted with a reciprocal step. On January 15, the 
Czech Republic introduced unilaterally visa regime in relation 
to Armenia, Azerbaijan, Georgia and Tajikistan. 

</TEXT>

