<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Joint Russian-U.S. Military Exercise Called Off </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Joint Russian-U.S. Military Exercise Called Off </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2006163094 Moscow Radio Moscow World Service in English 
1500 GMT 20 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2006163094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Moscow World Service </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The joint Russian-American military exercises slated 
for early next month in southern Russia in the area of the city 
of Orenburg have been cancelled. This was disclosed today by a 
spokesmen for the two sides. 
  Vladimir (Nikonorov), a spokesman for the Russian Defense 
Ministry, said that the cancellation was not his ministry's 
fault but was due to the resolution adopted by the Russian 
parliament's lower house, the State Duma. In his words, the 
Russian Government yielded to the pressure, although the idea 
itself had not been rejected. 
  Spokesman for the United States embassy in Moscow, Michael 
McClellan, said the joint exercises are postponed and work is 
currently underway to determine a fresh date. He expressed hope 
that these would still take place in Russia elsewhere, possibly 
in autumn. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

