<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Naval Exercises Held Near Vladivostok </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Naval Exercises Held Near Vladivostok </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2006210894 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1830 GMT 
20 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2006210894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In the Far East, 20 miles to the south of 
Vladivostok, the Russian-U.S. naval exercises Cooperation at Sea 
'94 are taking place. According to the Russian Navy press 
center, the exercises include work on joint actions to aid 
people caught in calamitous circumstances. 
  The United States is being represented by the landing craft 
Dubuque with 250 marines aboard. The marines are headed by Rear 
Admiral John Seagler, commander of amphibious forces for the 
Western Group of the U.S. 7th Fleet. The Russians taking part 
consist of a large landing craft of the Pacific Fleet and 180 
marines. 
  Rear Admiral Nikolay Kocherginin, commander of the 
Association of Pacific Fleet Landing Craft, is responsible for 
the general supervision of the exercises, which will continue 
until 23 June. 

</TEXT>

