Debuc with marines and 12 boats under the command of Rear 
Admiral John Siegler. 
  Officers in the Russian navy's press center told INTERFAX 
that the ships were already in the area where the exercise was 
to be carried out and would start the "humanitarian landing" at 
7:00 local time on June 21. 

