<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   DPRK Not To Accept Inspection While Talks Under Way </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    DPRK Not To Accept Inspection While Talks Under Way </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2106081894 Seoul YONHAP in English 0755 GMT 21 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2106081894 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, June 21 (YONHAP) -- North Korea will not 
accept full-scale international inspection of its nuclear 
facilities while talks with the United States are underway, a 
senior North Korean diplomat said Monday. 
  North Korean Ambassador to Russia Son Song-pil, while 
explaining his country's position on the continuing nuclear row 
to members of the Russian State Duma (House of Representatives) 
Foreign Affairs Committee, said that international nuclear 
inspections would never be allowed until an across-the-board 
agreement on the issue was reached with the United States. 
  Pyongyang would not return to the Nuclear Non-proliferation 
Treaty (NPT) should international organizations fail to withdraw 
their move toward sanctions against it, Son added. 
  Son said, "economic sanctions, if taken against North Korea, 
will be regarded as a declaration of war...we will counter war 
with war." 

</TEXT>

