<H3> <TI>   Moscow Hopes For End of June Meeting on Bosnia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Moscow Hopes For End of June Meeting on Bosnia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2006144994 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1339 GMT 20 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2006144994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Diplomatic Panorama" feature] </F>
  [Text] Moscow hopes that the second ministerial meeting for 
Bosnia is going to take place before the end of June. This was 
disclosed in a Monday interview with INTERFAX by a high-ranking 
official at the Russian Foreign Ministry. 
  The G-7 summit in Naples at the beginning of July is the 
deadline before the foreign ministers of Russia, the USA, 
Britain, France, Germany, Greece and Belgium must get together, 
the official said. 
  The diplomat hopes that technical matters can be resolved in 
a matter of days and the working schedules of ministers 
coordinated. "There is a more difficult problem, though. All 
possible actions of each of the conflicting Bosnian sides must 
be predicted", he said. The international community should have 
something in store, if one or both conflicting sides reject the 
plan approved during the first ministerial meeting. 
  Under the plan Bosnian Serbs should get 49 percent of the 
territory and the federation of Muslims and Croats 51 percent. 
  The Russian diplomat felt that Geneva would again host the 
ministerial meeting. "The leaders of the conflicting sides will 
evidently also be invited to Geneva. It is not clear, however, 
whether they are going to attend the meeting or whether the 
ministers will find another way of communicating with them", the 
official said. 

</TEXT>

