<F P=102>   LD2006211794 Moscow Russian Television Network in Russian 
1920 GMT 20 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2006211794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Russian Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Vesti" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Following the two hour long talks and a dinner 
reception at the sumptuous villa of the head of the Italian 
Government today, Premier Viktor Chernomyrdin told journalists: 
Silvio Berlusconi is the most interesting man I have ever met. 
The conversation between the two men was very cordial and 
fruitful. Berlusconi accepted the invitation to come to Moscow 
on an official visit. In the course of the visit Russia and 
Italy will sign a friendship and cooperation treaty. According 
to Italian diplomats, the treaty envisages the kind of political 
and economic cooperation which Russia has only with Germany. 
Berlusconi assured Chernomyrdin that he would support Russia in 
her effort to join the group of seven developed nations, and 
generally do his very best to make Russia a leading country in 
the world scene. 
  In reply to the flattering remarks by Chernomyrdin, 
Berlusconi said that while engaging in personal cultural 
development he read more Russian than Italian writers. Today 
the Russian prime minister, who is now staying in Milan at the 
invitation of the Italian state oil company Eni, also took part 
in the 19th world congress on natural gas. 

</TEXT>

