<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Further on Kozyrev-Galanos Meeting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further on Kozyrev-Galanos Meeting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2006201994 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1839 
GMT 20 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2006201994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By diplomatic correspondent ITAR-TASS Dmitriy Gorokhov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 20 Jun--When Andrey Kozyrev received Alexis 
Galanos, chairman of the Cypriot House of Representatives, at 
the Russian Federation Foreign Ministry on 20 June, he said that 
the development of Russian-Cypriot dialogue was "very active." 
The present round of a regular exchange of opinions, which is 
taking place with the participation of the representatives of 
both the executive and the legislative powers, followed the 
talks between the Russian foreign minister and Cypriot Foreign 
Minister Alexandros Mikhailidhis, who visited Moscow during the 
first 10 days of June. 
  Kozyrev believes that the process of a comprehensive 
development of relations between the two countries is in keeping 
with the current "revival of spiritual and historical aims of 
Russia's foreign policy." Moscow and Nicosia have a similar 
point of view on many international problems. The head of the 
Russian diplomacy said, in particular, that they were going to 
continue providing assistance in the settlement of the Cypriot 
problem. In this instance, he said, the parties had a chance to 
compare their views and found out that their actions were 
similar. 
  Galina Sidorova, political adviser of the Russian minister, 
said to journalists that Nicosia acknowledged Moscow's positive 
role in the Cypriot settlement once again during the talks. One 
of the topics of conversation was a report prepared by the 
secretary general of the United Nations, which spells out all 
the aspects of the problem and proposes a plan of action that 
the world community could take in this matter. 
  According to her, Nicosia has taken a positive stance with 
regard to Russia's joining the Council of Europe. Beginning in 
November, Cyprus will be chairing the foreign ministers 
committee of the Council of Europe, and our partners have 
stressed their determination to facilitate this process. 

</TEXT>

