BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed untitled report] </F>
  [Text] According to the investigation's theory, the 
attempt on the life of Moscow City Duma Deputy Nikolay 
Moskovchenko was made by persons from the Tajik antigovernment 
opposition, informed sources in the Moscow prosecutor's office 
have disclosed. According to a source, the suspects were in 
Moscow as part of a criminal gang connected with the drugs and 
arms trade. Composite pictures of some of the gang members 
suspected of the crime have been compiled, and a Russia-wide 
hunt for them is under way. "We know who we are looking for, 
but it will not be easy to catch them because they are migrant 
elements, and by now they may already be in Afghanistan," the 
source pointed out. 

