<F P=100> Federal Assembly </F>
<H3> <TI>   Federation Council Declines To Debate Budget </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Federation Council Declines To Debate Budget </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2106083194 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0808 GMT 21 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2106083194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS parliamentary correspondent Lyudmila Yermakova] </F>
  [Text] Moscow June 21 TASS -- The Upper House of the 
Russian Parliament has declined to include an item about the 
country's federal budget for 1994 on its agenda today. 
  Federation Council Chairman Vladimir Shumeyko told the 
chamber that the Lower House, the State Duma which approved the 
budget upon second reading, failed to forward it to the Upper 
House. 
  The Federation Council speaker also informed the members 
that 
the Duma refused to hear the Upper House Budget Committee 
Chairman Nikolay Gonchar who wanted to inform the Duma about 
objections to some articles of the federal budget. 
  According to Shumeyko, the State Duma plans to return to the 
draft budget before forwarding it to the Upper House of the 
Russian legislature. 
  The Federation Council decided to hear Nikolay Gonchar's 
report on Tuesday afternoon and call upon the Duma to take due 
account of the proposals made by Federation Council members. 
  The debate about the proposed budget is nonetheless likely 
to 
take part when the chamber goes down to the "any other business" 
item under pressure of the pickets outside the building who 
demand prompt support for the defence industry. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

