<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Duma To Hold Hearings on Closed Cities Problems </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MK2106060094 Moscow SEGODNYA in Russian 21 Jun 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> MK2106060094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow SEGODNYA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Yuriy Rogozhin report: "Prospect of Closed Cities"] </F>
  [Text] The State Duma council has decided to hold 
hearings, before the parliament recess, on the problem of closed 
cities -- there are more than 100 of them in Russia and their 
population is several million. All the nuclear-and 
defense-related cities face the same problems -- falling 
production, unemployment, environmental pollution. The 
committee for industry, energy, and transport is planning, as 
part of preparations for the hearing, to hold a conference in 
Tomsk-7 at the end of June with representatives of the other 
closed cities and interested departments. 

</TEXT>

