<F P=100> Federal Assembly </F>
<H3> <TI>   Zhirinovskiy Presents Privatization Concept to Duma </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Zhirinovskiy Presents Privatization Concept to Duma </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1706152094 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1419 GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1706152094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Liberal Democratic Party's [LDP] faction is 
demanding that the Duma act promptly to prevent the 
privatization program for 1994-1996 from taking effect in 
disregard of the constitution and the Duma. The demand, which 
comes in a statement by the faction leader Vladimir 
Zhirinovskiy, was circulated in the parliament's lower house 
today. 
  He says that on June 14 the Privatization Commission of the 
State Property Committee approved the privatization concept and 
program devised under the guidance of the commission's Chairman 
Anatoliy Chubays and drafted a decree on how to implement this 
program. 
  He reports that his faction has prepared an alternative 
concept for the president, government, and Security Council and 
insists on giving it as much publicity as the government's 
package. 
  The LDP faction maintains that the Duma should 
differentially 
distribute incomes from privatization and denationalization and 
proposes that the State Property Committee be abolished and a 
committee to oversee property relations be set up and a state 
committee be formed to control Russia's property abroad. The 
Liberal Democrats also want all privatization profits, including 
those remitted abroad, to be progressively taxed. To cut the 
budget deficit, they consider it necessary to slash aid to 
former Soviet republics. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

