<F P=100> CENTRAL ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Kazakhstan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Nazarbayev Speaks on Ways of Overcoming Crisis </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Nazarbayev Speaks on Ways of Overcoming Crisis </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2006161094 Almaty Kazakh Radio Network in Kazakh 1400 GMT 
20 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2006161094 </F>
<F P=104>  Almaty Kazakh Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Kazakh </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Nursultan Nazarbayev visited East Kazakhstan and 
Semipalatinsk oblasts at the end of last week. He introduced 
the new head of the regional administration Yuriy Lavrinenko at 
a meeting in Ust-Kamenogorsk. Then he left for Semipalatinsk 
where he introduced the new head of the regional administration 
Galymzhan Zhakyanov. During a meeting there Nazarbayev briefed 
his audience on the current economic situation in the Republic. 
He said that we should toughen up control over credit 
allocation to enterprises so as to speed up the process of 
lifting the country's economy out of crisis. The existing 
economic situation should be taken into account in addressing 
any issue. 
  In a message to parliamentarians Nazarbayev dwelled on ways 
of overcoming the crisis. He paid special attention to the need 
for stability in society. This stability can be maintained 
provided all citizens have equal opportunities and a careful 
personnel policy based on regional characteristics is carried 
out. The main thing is not to allow any kind of provocations, 
and to observe the law on bringing charges against those who 
inflame national feelings. The president answered all the 
questions during the meetings. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

