<F P=100> CENTRAL ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Kazakhstan </F>
<H3> <TI>   IMF Loans $30 Million to Reconstruct Oil-Production System </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    IMF Loans $30 Million to Reconstruct Oil-Production System </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2006145794 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1306 GMT 20 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2006145794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The International Monetary Fund has extended $30 
million to the Kazakh oil and gas amalgamation Mangistaumunaigaz 
to be used for the reconstruction of the oil-production system 
in Uzen (western Kazakhstan). 
  Experts told the Oil Information Agency that the IMF credit 
would be invested in the construction of a facility for 
collecting oil leakage and oil-industry wastes, and for 
processing them into quality gasoline. 
  Kazakhstan's Department for Environmental Protection and 
Biological Resources reports that more than 16,000 square meters 
of fertile soil has been polluted in Uzen. The oil pools are 
polluting the air with hydrogen sulphide, whose content exceeds 
the admissible level. 

</TEXT>

