<F P=100> CAUCASUS </F>
<F P=101> Armenia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Consumer Market Prices Increase </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Consumer Market Prices Increase </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2006193894 Yerevan SNARK in English 1208 GMT 20 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2006193894 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan SNARK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Yerevan. [dateline as received] Price growth at the 
consumer market of Armenia is going on. The State Department of 
Statistics told SNARK the growth of foodstuff prices in May made 
up 65.3 percent, as compared with April. The specialists 
mention that the prices on bread increased more than two times, 
on fruit -- 1.8 times, on vegetables and potatoes -- 1.6 times. 
During the same period (April-May 1994) the prices on 
manufactured goods increased 25 percent. Thus, the prices on 
non-ferrous metallurgy production increased 66.6 percent, food 
industry -- 52.3 percent, power engineering -- 41.6 percent, 
industry of building materials -- 31.9 percent. The tariffs in 
the chemical, oil and biotechnology industries increased 2.2 
times. The average growth of prices on manufactured goods in 
May 1994 made up 57.4 percent, as compared with last May. 

</TEXT>

