<H3> <TI>   Russian Military Begins Clearing Mines on Abkhaz Border </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russian Military Begins Clearing Mines on Abkhaz Border </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2006194094 Yerevan SNARK in English 1305 GMT 20 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2006194094 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan SNARK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Russian Specialists Began Clearing of Mines on the </F>
Georgian- Abkhazian Border"-- SNARK headline] 
  [Text] Moscow, June 20 (SNARK) -- Moscow field-engineer 
battalion started clear of mine works of the observers' 
stationing sites at the Georgian-Abkhazian border. Abkhazian 
Representation to Moscow informed of it SNARK today. 
  The complete entrance of the peace-keeping forces can begin 
only after the positive decision of this question in the 
Russia's Council of Federation on June 21. 
  Plenipotentiary Representative of Abkhazia to Moscow Igor 
Akhba told SNARK that "Abkhazia, as well as Georgia expect the 
decision of the Council of Federation and hope that the 
deployment of peace- keeping forces will positively influence 
the peace and stability in the region". 
  Moscow military specialists forecast the Council of 
Federation will adopt the decision on sending peace-keeping 
forces to the zone of Georgian-Abkhazian conflict. 

</TEXT>

