<H3> <TI>   Russian Peacekeeping Troops Reduced in S. Ossetia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russian Peacekeeping Troops Reduced in S. Ossetia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2006165094 Tbilisi IBERIA in Georgian 1430 GMT 20 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2006165094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tbilisi IBERIA </F>
<F P=105>  Georgian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tskhinvali 20 [dateline as received] -- Peacekeeping 
forces stationed in the Tskhinvali region have undergone 
changes. While up to 1,000 Russian airborne assault troops were 
stationed in the region in 1992, only 523 soldiers of a motor 
rifle battalion of the Russian Armed Forces are involved in the 
peacekeeping operations there at the moment. 
  The commanders of the Russian peacekeeping forces have said 
that they cannot stay in the region permanently. Therefore, 
Ossetians and Georgians should find a common language promptly 
to ensure a political settlement the current conflict. 

</TEXT>

