<H3> <TI>   Refugees Support Call for Peacekeeping Forces </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Refugees Support Call for Peacekeeping Forces </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MK2106074094 Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA in Russian 21 Jun 94 
p 3 </F>

<F P=103> MK2106074094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Untitled report under the "NEGA Reports" rubric] </F>
  [Text] In the wake of last week's incident in parliament, 
the indignant refugees making their temporary home in the city 
of Zugdidi and Zugdidi Rayon have addressed to Eduard 
Shevardnadze a brief letter supporting the head of state's 
actions aimed at a peaceful settlement of the Abkhazian 
conflict. "Enough bloodshed, enough casualties, our material 
and moral resources have long been exhausted," the letter says. 
"The refugees have reached the point where they have begun 
begging." The documents [as published] are signed by several 
hundred people driven to desperation, they voice their 
indignation at the irresponsibility of opposition-minded 
deputies and their "jingoist speeches" in parliament. "We ask 
you to take all the necessary measures for a timely and 
unimpeded bringing in of peacekeeping forces and their 
deployment in Abkhazia," the authors of the letter insist. 

</TEXT>

