<F P=100> Latvia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Interim Agreement on Noncitizens Approved With Russia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Interim Agreement on Noncitizens Approved With Russia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2006181294 Riga Radio Riga Network in Latvian 1700 GMT 20 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2006181294 </F>
<F P=104>  Riga Radio Riga Network </F>
<F P=105>  Latvian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Foreign Affairs and Security Committee of the 
Latvian Cabinet of Ministers today approved an interim agreement 
between the Latvian and Russian Governments on travel from 
Latvia to Russia, and return to places of permanent residence in 
Latvia of citizens of the former USSR who are neither citizens 
of Latvia nor citizens of Russia nor citizens of a third 
country. According to the interim agreement, the 
above-mentioned people will be able to travel to Russia without 
visas and return to Latvia showing documents stating their 
identity. The passport of the former USSR, which has an entry 
in it about a person's place of permanent residence in Latvia, 
will ensure visa-free return to Latvia. 
  Apart from this, the Committee also approved an agreement 
between Latvia and Russia on the work of border representatives, 
which envisages nomination of plenipotentiary representatives of 
the two states for settling incidents that have occurred on the 
border and for tackling problems related to the border. The 
agreement provides that each side nominates one plenipotentiary 
border representative and two deputies, who will consider 
problems arising on the border at conferences after a proposal 
from either side. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

