<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Vladas Burbulis] </F>
  [Text] Vilnius June 20 TASS -- "An intention expressed by 
the head of the U.S. Administration to meet leaders of the three 
Baltic states in Riga on July 6 shows that the United States has 
recognised and respects our independence," said Lithuanian 
President Algirdas Brazauskas in a traditional interview on 
national radio on Monday. 
  "I have received a very kind message to this effect from 
Bill 
Clinton in which he confirms the fact of his arrival in Riga and 
his wish to meet the presidents of Latvia, Lithuania and 
Estonia," Brazauskas said. 
  The Lithuanian president expects to discuss with Bill 
Clinton 
regional problems and hopes for Clinton's support which "has 
been felt until now." 
  Brazauskas added that "we would attempt once again to 
acquaint the U.S. president with the conditions for foreign 
investments into the Lithuanian economy, which, in our opinion, 
are not bad and which we are going to improve, taking into 
account the experience of Central European states." 

