<H3> <TI>   Defense Minister Seeks Support From Chicago Community </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Defense Minister Seeks Support From Chicago Community </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2006164394 Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service in Ukrainian 
1500 GMT 20 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2006164394 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The head of a Ukrainian military delegation, Defense 
Minister Vitaliy Radetskyy, has held several meetings in 
Washington's White House. Intensive talks at different levels 
have been held during the Ukrainian delegation's official visit 
to the United States, the Ukrainian Defense Ministry Press 
Service reports. In Chicago, Vitaliy Radetskyy and his 
colleagues were warmly greeted by the local Ukrainian community. 
In his address to its members, Radetskyy dwelled in detail on 
the course of Ukraine's army building. He stressed that the 
present state of military and technical capability in the 
Ukrainian Armed Forces is quite sufficient for the defense of 
the Ukrainian state. At the same time, Radetskyy pointed out 
the problems of servicemen's social protection. The most urgent 
of these, he said, is the housing problem, in the solving of 
which Ukraine could use, as far as possible, the assistance of 
the Ukrainian community in the United States. 

</TEXT>

