<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Nuclear Commission Chairman on NPT Treaty </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Nuclear Commission Chairman on NPT Treaty </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2106092194 Kiev UNIAN in Ukrainian 1930 GMT 20 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2106092194 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAN </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kiev -- Mykhaylo Pavlovskyy, chairman of Ukraine's 
Supreme Council Commission for Nuclear Safety and Nuclear 
Policy, informed a UNIAN correspondent in an interview on 20 
June that the main tasks now facing the commission are the 
organization of the safe work of nuclear power stations (the 
burial of nuclear waste is included in this too) and the 
elaboration of a concept of the development of power engineering 
as a whole, and nuclear power in particular. 
  Regarding parliament's possible rejection of Ukraine's 
accession to the Nuclear Nonproliferation Treaty [NPT] as a 
non-nuclear state, Pavlovskyy replied: "This issue will not be 
raised. There can be no going back." (As UNIAN has already 
reported, deputies from the Union of Officers of Ukraine are to 
address an initiative to parliament on Ukraine returning to 
nuclear status.) 
  Concerning international assistance in converting facilities 
of the military-industrial complex, in the opinion of the 
commission chairman, efficient assistance is that which is 
directed at specific programs. However, he believes that one 
can hardly expect such targeted assistance in the near future. 

</TEXT>

