<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Deputy Minister, No. Ossetia President Hold Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Deputy Minister, No. Ossetia President Hold Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1706151894 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1442 GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1706151894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Valeriy Shanayev] </F>
  [Text] Vladikavkaz June 17 TASS -- At a meeting held here 
today between North Ossetian President Akhsarbek Galazov and 
Russian First Deputy Interior Minister Colonel-General Yevgeniy 
Abramov, they discussed the implementation of the Russian 
presidential decree on "the introduction of an emergency 
situation in a part of the territory of the North Ossetian and 
Ingush republics" issued on May 30, 1994. 
  This document empowers the Russian Interior Ministry, the 
Federal Counter-espionage Service and the provisional 
administration forces from the russian defence ministry, to take 
measures to prevent armed clashes between hostile sides, to 
ensure the safety of civilians and the strict observance of the 
emergency rules and regulations. 
  According to Yevgeniy Abramov, the Russian presidential 
decree on the return of refugees and Russian Federation 
Government decisions to implementing the decree must be carried 
out. However, refugees should not be simply returned to their 
villages, but their security and normal living conditions should 
also be ensured. The minister expressed concern over the large 
quantity of arms possessed by the population, and over the 
activities of unlawful armed formations, which are trying to 
destabilize the situation and undermine the implementation of 
the Russian presidential decree. 

</TEXT>

