<H3> <TI>   Far East Leaders Discuss Draft Presidential Edict </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Far East Leaders Discuss Draft Presidential Edict </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM2006131994 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 18 Jun 94 
First Edition p 1 </F>

<F P=103> PM2006131994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Item from roundup of ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA, ITAR-TASS reports </F>
under the "Yesterday, Today, Tomorrow" rubric: "Far Easterners 
Discuss Incentives"] 
  [Text] A draft presidential edict "On Special Measures in 
Managing the Socioeconomic Development of the Far East and 
Transbaykal in 1994-1995" was discussed yesterday at a session 
of the Interregional Association for Economic Collaboration 
Between Federation Components in the Far East and Transbaykal. 
  Territory leaders believe that it is essential to set 
uniform 
electricity and heat tariffs for Siberia and the Far East, to 
recompense from the budget 50 percent of the expenditure 
incurred both on importing fuel and foodstuffs into the region 
and on exporting produce made here, and to repay the debt owed 
by the federal budget to state sector enterprises. The draft 
also provides for restrictions on tax deductions from profits, 
and customs and tax incentives. 

</TEXT>

