<H3> <TI>   Funds Made Available To Pay Defense Workers' Wages </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Funds Made Available To Pay Defense Workers' Wages </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM2006133594 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 18 Jun 94 
First Edition p 2 </F>

<F P=103> PM2006133594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Wages for South Urals Defense </F>
Workers"] 
  [Text] Some 230 billion rubles have been transferred for 
the express purposes of extinguishing indebtedness in respect of 
wages due to workers at defense enterprises in the South Urals. 
This was announced by Deputy Finance Minister Andrey Astakhov 
at a joint sitting of the government commission, the Chelyabinsk 
Oblast leadership, and defense sector enterprise directors. 
Thus, the first step toward remedying the critical situation 
prevailing here has been taken. 
  The arrival of an authoritative Russian Government 
commission 
at one of the country's leading industrial regions and its tour 
of a number of major enterprises and the Defense Complex Design 
Bureau was seen by Igor Velichko, general designer at the State 
Missile Center, as a show of genuine interest on the part of the 
leadership of ministries and departments in ensuring the 
stabilization of the work of the military-industrial complex. 

</TEXT>

