<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Mikhail Gorbunov: "Kolyma Unites"] </F>
  [Text] Magadan -- A new political association has been 
registered in Magadan Oblast. It is called "Civic Union of 
Kolyma." It includes representatives of sundry political 
parties and movements from the region which have addressed a 
"statement" to northerners setting out the union's basic program 
provisions. 
  Just the other day the second stage of elections to the 
Oblast Duma and Magadan City Duma were held in the oblast. The 
elections, in which 27 percent of the voters took part, were 
successful. Former USSR Supreme Soviet Deputy Vladimir Yudin and 
a number of his colleagues from the "Civic Union of Kolyma" 
became Duma deputies. More than half the Duma members are heads 
of rayon administrations and personnel from the oblast's state 
structures. One of the main topics in the election program was 
the preservation of the economic and social potential of one of 
the principal northern regions. 

</TEXT>

