<H3> <TI>   Filatov, Kostikov Attend RDCP Founding Congress </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Filatov, Kostikov Attend RDCP Founding Congress </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1206163794 Moscow RIA in English 1512 GMT 12 Jun 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD1206163794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow RIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, June 12, RIA -- Russian President's Press 
Secretary Vyacheslav Kostikov and Head of the Presidential 
Administration Sergey Filatov were present today at the founding 
congress of Russia's Democratic Choice Party [RDCP]. However, 
neither did they address the congress, nor did they make any 
statements on the president's behalf. 
  "I'm not a bit surprised that Russia's Democratic Choice 
Party has received no congratulations on its creation. Our 
relations with him (the president) are good and constructive 
enough so as to do without such curtsies," the party's leader, 
Yegor Gaydar, told a briefing today. 
  "Such congratulation messages are usually prepared by those 
being congratulated," Sergey Filatov told a RIA correspondent, 
adding that it's not worth paying that much attention to the 
absence of such a message. 

</TEXT>

