<H3> <TI>   Kozyrev Intends To Visit Brussels `Soon' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kozyrev Intends To Visit Brussels `Soon' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1406124194 Moscow RIA in English 1046 GMT 14 Jun 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD1406124194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow RIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, June 14, RIA -- Russian Foreign Minister 
Andrey Kozyrev intends to visit Brussels soon, he said in an 
interview today to a RIA correspondent. 
  During the visit the Russian minister expects to meet U.S. 
Secretary of State Warren Christopher. Kozyrev will discuss 
with the NATO leadership the questions of signing a NATO frame 
document for the Partnership for Peace and a Moscow-proposed 
programme of strategic cooperation between Russia and NATO. The 
latter document would determine the main documents of 
Russia-NATO cooperation with regard to the role and weight of 
Moscow in world affairs. 
  We believe, noted the Russian minister, that it is necessary 
to sign both documents simultaneously and will be ready to do it 
depending on how soon the entire required preparatory work will 
be completed in NATO headquarters. Kozyrev said that he could 
not give the precise date of his visit to Brussels since this 
question has to be agreed with all the parties concerned. 

</TEXT>

