<H3> <TI>   Russian Pilots Join Bosnians; Ministry Declines Comment </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russian Pilots Join Bosnians; Ministry Declines Comment </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1506151194 Moscow RIA in English 1313 GMT 15 Jun 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD1506151194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow RIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Paris, June 15, RIA -- [AGENCE] FRANCE PRESSE 
reported today, citing Western military sources and an anonymous 
representative of the Bosnian Army, two Russian mercenary 
pilots, employed by the Serbs, joined the Moslem Bosnian Army. 
They landed their Mi-17 helicopters at the headquarters of the 
3rd Corps of the Bosnian Army in Zenic, bringing along presents 
designed to show their good will, said a Bosnian officer. The 
two Russian pilots do not intend to take part in hostilities in 
Bosnia. It is the first case when Russians fighting on the side 
of the Serbs turned over to Moslems, the agency writes. The 
Russian Defence Ministry refused to comment. 

</TEXT>

