<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rutskoy Criticizes Edict </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rutskoy Criticizes Edict </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1706173294 Moscow NTV in Russian 1500 GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1706173294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow NTV </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] President Yeltsin's edict on fighting banditry and 
organized crime is accumulating an ever larger number of 
opinions. Former vice president Aleksandr Rutskoy, the famous 
champion of the fight against corruption, has not remained on 
the sidelines. Presently in Krasnoyarsk, Rutskoy, chairman of 
the Russian Social Democratic People's Party, has criticized 
this edict. One of his arguments is: Name me a single document 
which could be implemented, Rutskoy said in an interview to a 
RIA correspondent. Rutskoy believes that the edict has not been 
thoroughly worked out, and not only violates human rights, but 
is contradictory to legislation. With the aid of the edict, the 
authorities intend to drive society into a condition of total 
pathological fear, Rutskoy said. 

</TEXT>

