<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin, Kozyrev, Yerin Visit Crack Police Division </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin, Kozyrev, Yerin Visit Crack Police Division </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1806120094 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1136 GMT 18 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1806120094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow June 18 TASS -- President Yeltsin visited 
today a special crack police division of the Interior Ministry 
troops (the former Dzerzhinskiy Division). 
  On the occasion of the 70th anniversary of the creation of 
the division, the commander-in-chief viewed the parade of the 
division's personnel and the performance of the special task 
force. The president was invited to have lunch at the soldiers' 
canteen and had a conversation with servicemen. 
  He was accompanied by Interior Minister Viktor Yerin and 
Foreign Minister Andrey Kozyrev. 
  The history of the division is inseparably connected with 
the 
history of Russia and Moscow, its capital. Several generations 
of officers and men, serving in the division, fulfilled their 
duty with dignity. Nineteen of them were awarded the titles of 
the hero of the Soviet Union and hero of the Russian Federation, 
thousands were awarded orders and medals. 
  Yeltsin sent today a congratulatory message to soldiers, 
sergeants, non-commissioned officers, officers and veterans of 
the division. 
  "By successfully carrying out your tasks, especially during 
the troublesome recent years, you contributed a great deal to 
the preservation of civil peace in the country. I am confident 
that you will continue to ensure public security, acting jointly 
with other branches of the Interior Ministry, in the interests 
of the consolidation of the Russian state," the message said. 

</TEXT>

