<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Yuriy Shcherban] </F>
  [Text] Moscow June 21 TASS -- At the trial of Valentin 
Varennikov, former commander-in-chief of Soviet Land Forces and 
deputy minister of defence, the military panel of the Supreme 
Court on Tuesday endorsed the defendant's application requesting 
that additional witnesses be summoned. 
  Former KGB chief Vladimir Kryuchkov and former prime 
minister 
Valentin Pavlov have been invited as witnesses for the study of 
circumstances of the meeting at ABC facility on the eve of the 
formation of the self-proclaimed emergency committee. 
  Yuriy Plekhanov and Vyacheslav Generalov will be called to 
the court as witnesses to clarify the circumstances of the 
disconnection of government communications in the Crimea and the 
isolation of Soviet President Mikhail Gorbachev. The two 
already appeared as witnesses at the coup plotters' trial. 
  Other witnesses will also be invited to the court, including 
those suggested by Arkadiy Denisov, senior military prosecutor 
at the main department for the exercise of supervision in the 
armed forces, who represents the prosecution. 
  The hearing of the case goes on. 

</TEXT>

