<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Economic Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Consumer Price Inflation Continues To Slow Down </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Consumer Price Inflation Continues To Slow Down </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM2106105594 Moscow IZVESTIYA in Russian 21 Jun 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> PM2106105594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow IZVESTIYA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Price Rises Continue To Slow"] </F>
  [Text] The Russian State Committee for Statistics reports 
that the increase in prices of consumer goods and services 
during the period from 8 through 14 June was the smallest since 
the beginning of the year: 0.8 percent. During that week food 
prices rose by 0.7 percent, nonfood prices rose by 0.9 percent, 
and prices of consumer services rose by one percent. 
  The cost of the basket of 19 basic foodstuffs was 56,000 
rubles [R] for one month's consumption. The maximum cost of the 
basket was R150,400 in Magadan, and the minimum was R35,800 in 
Ulyanovsk. Since the beginning of the year the cost of 
individual types of housing and municipal services has increased 
six to eight times, the cost of travel on trains and city buses 
has increased four to five times, the cost of places in 
children's preschool establishments has trebled, and it is now 
twice as expensive to stay in sanatoriums and recreation centers. 

</TEXT>

