<F P=106> [From the "Vesti" newscast] </F>
  [Text] In May, the Russian Government's budget owed 
enterprises 8.5 trillion rubles. The figure was mentioned 
during a session of the public chamber of the Russian president 
by Aleksandr Shokhin, deputy prime minister and minister for the 
economy in the government. 
  The deputy prime minister believes that using privatization 
income to set up an extra-budgetary fund, which could be put 
into anything from the defense sector to the socio-cultural 
sphere, could be one way out of the difficult financial 
situation. 

