<F P=106> [Report by INTERFAX: "Unprofitable Mines Will Be Closed"] </F>
  [Text] This year Russia will earmark 305 billion rubles 
for closing unprofitable coal mines. For the first time the 
Russian state budget envisages a separate category for 
expenditure on such objectives. 
  In the near future, according to "Rosugol" Company Deputy 
Chairman N. Garkavenko, there are plans to complete work on 
closing down five unprofitable pits, including pits in the 
Pechora coal field. Another six pits will be shut down before 
the end of 1995. 

