<H3> <TI>   Two Battalions of Peacekeepers on Standby for Abkhazia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Two Battalions of Peacekeepers on Standby for Abkhazia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2106112794 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1006 GMT 21 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2106112794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Two Russian battalions in the Caucuses are fully 
prepared for peace-keeping operation in the Georgian-Abkhaz 
conflict zone, Interfax learned Tuesday at the press center of 
the Russian forces. 
  The center said that the batallions were ready to take 
control of the area allotted to them within a few hours of 
receiving orders. 
  The order could come immediately following the Federation 
Council's approval of the decision of President Yeltsin to send 
peace-keepers to Georgia. 

</TEXT>

