<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Officials Claim DPRK `Does Not Have Nuclear Arms' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Officials Claim DPRK `Does Not Have Nuclear Arms' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2106135294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1341 GMT 21 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2106135294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Veronika Romanenkova] </F>
  [Text] Moscow June 21 TASS -- Specialists from the Russian 
Ministry for Nuclear Power Engineering are sure that North Korea 
does not have nuclear arms, head of the ministry's department 
Georgiy Kaurov told a news conference here today. At the same 
time, he stressed that every state that has a nuclear reactor is 
potentially able to make an A-bomb. 
  The North Korean nuclear center was created with the use of 
technical documents and the assistance of Soviet nuclear 
specialists, Vladislav Kotlov, the ministry's leading expert and 
supervisor of the North Korean center's construction, told the 
news conference. 
  In his words, the center is meant for exclusively economic 
and scientific purposes, it produces isotopes for medicine and 
industry, processes the results of physical experiments, 
develops technologies and trains specialists. Today the center 
does not have a single Russian specialist. 
  "Any nuclear installation is capable to produce plutonium", 
said Kotlov. But it is necessary to build a number of 
facilities, train specialists and have kilos of plutonium to use 
the installation for the defence. 
  The expert said that North Korea is building the facilities 
and has nuclear specialists. But it has produced several dozens 
or hundreds of grams of plutonium which is not enough to make a 
nuclear bomb, he added. 
  In his turn, Kaurov thinks that one cannot say the nuclear 
arms are ready before they are tested. It is up to a sovereign 
state whether or not to admit IAEA inspectors to its secret 
facilities. Russia also has a number of centers which foreign 
specialists are not allowed to visit, he added. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

