<H3> <TI>   Meets U.S. Jewish Leaders </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Meets U.S. Jewish Leaders </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2206041994 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 0300 GMT 
22 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2206041994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The head of the Russian Government Viktor 
Chernomyrdin, who arrived in Washington on a visit on Tuesday, 
held a meeting in his official residence with representatives of 
influential Jewish organizations. The leaders of the 
organizations stated their support for the process of Russian 
reforms and stressed that they would do everything possible to 
assist them. At the same time they voiced concern at rising 
crime in Russia and acts of anti-Semitism. 
  Viktor Chernomyrdin stated that the country's leadership 
intends to firmly strive for the observance of human rights and 
to combat crime and manifestations of chauvinism. At the same 
time he noted that political stability can be based only on 
economic stability and economic and trade cooperation between 
Russia and the Unites States could play an immense role here. 
  At the meeting a wide range of issues was discussed, in 
particular the need for the abolition of the Jackson-Vanick 
amendment as one of the barriers which are holding back the 
development of bilateral trade. 

</TEXT>

