<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kozyrev Notes Lack of Single Foreign Economic Strategy </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kozyrev Notes Lack of Single Foreign Economic Strategy </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2106172594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1544 GMT 21 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2106172594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondents Tamara Zamyatina, </F>
Vladimir Smelov, and Viktor Khrekov] 
  [Text] Moscow June 21 TASS -- The Russian Foreign Ministry 
is ready and can help exports of Russian goods to the world 
market, however, the Ministry of Foreign Economic Relations does 
not help the Foreign Ministry in this respect, Russian Foreign 
Minister Andrey Kozyrev told a meeting of editors-in-chief of 
Russian mass media bodies here today. 
  That is why, the Foreign Ministry does not even know what 
state is the most efficient economic partner for Russia, he 
added. 
  In the words of Andrey Kozyrev, a single state strategy for 
Russian entrance to the world market has not been elaborated 
since the time of Eduard Shevardnadze was Soviet foreign 
minister. "If we receive a corresponding concept from the 
minister of foreign economic relations, we could act in the 
Russian economic interests. Politics always influences the 
economy," said Kozyrev. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

