BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS] </F>
  [Text] Moscow June 22 TASS -- President Boris Yelisin 
received Mr Federico Mayor, director-general of the United 
Nations Educational, Scientific and Cultural Organisation 
(UNESCO), in the Kremlin on Wednesday and presented the Peoples' 
Friendship Order to him "for a big contribution to the 
development of international intellectual cooperation in the 
name of peace and progress", the presidential press service 
announced. 
  Yeltsin reaffirmed Russia's invariable support for this 
international organisation as a unique forum for international 
cooperation in culture, science, education and communications. 
Considering democratic processes in Russia, Yeltsin emphasised 
his interest in a success of UNESCO's world culture programme. 
  The UNESCO chief told the Russian president in detail about 
UNESCO activities in the coming year 1995 which has been 
designated by UNESCO as the year of tolerance. 

