<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Governors Seek Talks With Yeltsin on Economic Crisis </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Governors Seek Talks With Yeltsin on Economic Crisis </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2106164494 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1522 GMT 21 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2106164494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Lev Rumyantsev] </F>
  [Text] St. Petersburg June 21 TASS -- Russian governors 
will "insist on a soonest meeting with President Boris Yeltsin" 
to tell him about their opinion of ways out of the economic 
crisis, Leningrad Regional Governor Aleksandr Belyakov told 
ITAR-TASS today upon the completion of a governors' meeting in 
Novgorod. 
  "The president meets anyone but us, and we know the Russian 
life from inside," said Belyakov. In his words, the governors 
have elaborated 23 measures which, they believe, will help to 
overcome the economic crisis and they want to tell the president 
about that immediately. 
  The governors give a priority to the 10,000,000,000,000 
ruble 
emission to make the ruble/dollar correlation real and settle 
the non-payment problem a reason for which is the enterprises' 
lack of proceeds they have earned. 
  Anti-crisis proposals also include the introduction of a 
modern bill mechanism, state insurance of loans to the 
population, state control over the increased cost of energy 
carriers and cargo transportation, subordination of all federal 
structures in regions to the municipal authorities and the 
introduction of the governor status in Russia. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

