<F P=102>   LD2106172394 Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service in Ukrainian 
1600 GMT 21 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2106172394 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ukrainian President Leonid Kravchuk has addressed 
Russian President Boris Yeltsin, proposing to set up a 
Russian-Ukrainian oil company as a transnational corporation. 
The proposal was made after Kravchuk's visit to Lugansk's 
Lisichansk Petroleum Organic Synthesis joint stock company. He 
believes that setting up a transnational corporation would be 
another step along the path of strengthening friendship and 
developing cooperation between Ukraine and the Russian 
Federation. 
  The president of Ukraine familiarized himself with the state 
of affairs at the joint stock company. At a meeting with the 
enterprise's leadership, work force, and specialists, the 
prospects for the development of the oil processing sector and 
ways of curbing its economic crisis were discussed. 
  On the same day, Kravchuk met representatives of labor 
collectives, local authorities, parties, and movements from the 
towns of Lisichansk, Rubezhnoye, Pervomaysk, as well as 
(?Kalininskiy) and some other rayons of Lugansk Oblast. He 
described the economic situation in Ukraine, spoke about his 
vision for resolving current problems, and answered numerous 
questions from the electorate. 
  Participants in the meeting expressed themselves in support 
of the president's course and praised his plans of further 
nation building. 

</TEXT>

