<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Notes Lack of Free Trade With Russia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Ministry Notes Lack of Free Trade With Russia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2106173494 Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service in Ukrainian 
1600 GMT 21 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2106173494 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] About a year ago, a free trade agreement was signed 
between Ukraine and Russia. However, in reality there is no 
free trade. This was stated by Deputy Foreign Minister 
Oleksandr Makarenko at a Ukrainian Foreign Ministry briefing. 
He explained that there were 48 exceptions to the list of 
Russian goods imported by Ukraine. These goods, such as energy 
sources and timber, are vital to us. 
  The deputy minister believes that setting up a CIS economic 
union, and Ukraine being an associate member of this union, 
should end those discriminatory restrictions. 

</TEXT>

