<H3> <TI>   Government Approves Sale of Cartridges in West </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Approves Sale of Cartridges in West </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2106180694 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1546 GMT 21 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2106180694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondent Galina Nekrasova] </F>
  [Text] Lvov 21 June TASS -- According to the UNIAN 
independent Ukrainian news agency, the Lugansk-based 
machine-building works set going production of cartridges for 
submachine guns and pistols, including those of calibre 7.62, 
which are in great demand by foreign customers. 
  For example, a Cambodian entrepreneur has ordered 10 million 
cartridges of this calibre; the Dutch have ordered even more -- 
50 million cartridges. 
  To retool the Lugansk-based plant as soon as possible, the 
"Ukrinmash" foreign trade company, which has a licence for 
selling this kind of production, proposed that 10-20 million 
cartridges (the so-called untouchable reserve) be taken from the 
depots of Ukrainian Defence Ministry and sold in the West. The 
Ukrainian Government has already given a go-ahead for the move. 

</TEXT>

