<H3> <TI>   Candidate Urges Maximum Economic Independence for Crimea </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Candidate Urges Maximum Economic Independence for Crimea </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2206114494 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1005 GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2206114494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Crimea must be given the maximum of economic 
independence. This is a condition for settlement of the Crimean 
issue, said Vladimir Lanovoy, who is a candidate for the 
Ukrainian presidency. 
  Lanovoy said during a meeting with the Economic Council 
under 
the Crimean president that most tax revenues must remain in 
Crimea and be used for local needs. 
  During his visit to Crimea Lanovoy met with representatives 
of the Crimean-Tatar parliament and discussed the issue 
concerning compensation for the damage caused by the state to 
the deported and oppressed peoples returning to Crimea. 

</TEXT>

