<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Lanovyy Views Current Political, Economic Issues </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Lanovyy Views Current Political, Economic Issues </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2106183394 Kiev UNIAN in Ukrainian 1530 GMT 21 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2106183394 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAN </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Summary] Simferopol -- On 20 June presidential candidate 
Volodymyr Lanovyy visited Crimea where he met Viktor Mezhak, the 
deputy chairman of the Crimean Supreme Council. He also took 
part in a meeting of the higher economic council, which was was 
formed on 19 June under the Crimean Supreme Council presidium. 
  In his speeches Volodymyr Lanovyy supported the idea of 
democracy and economic regionalization. In his view, it is 
necessary to give the regions the right of autonomy in budgetary 
and tax affairs. He supported the idea of private ownership of 
land, but in the form of shares in collective or cooperative 
farms. 
  Speaking about his economic program, Volodymyr Lanovyy said 
that the duties on exports and imports are very high and that he 
would abolish export duties. As regards import duties, he 
considered that it should be no higher than 5 percent. He also 
believes there should be no restrictions on trade with the 
exception of those on strategic goods. 

</TEXT>

